                        <summary><p>AIM, southern shrine; on the base of the northern façade of the sanctuary and the <foreign>ardha-maṇḍapa</foreign>, begins below the niche of Brahmā; four lines are engraved on the round part of the base (<foreign>kumuda</foreign>), and six lines on the flat lower part of the base (<foreign>jagati</foreign>); 15th regnal year of Kōpparakesarivarman Uṭaiyar Śrī Rājendracōḻadeva = Rājendracōḻa I (<foreign>circa</foreign> 1027 A.D.); <foreign>meykkīrtti</foreign> of Rājendracōḻa, lines 1 to 6; because the inscription is built over at the end, I cannot give a continuous translation.</p></summary>
                        
                    </msContents>
